求求宅家的各位们放过“烘焙”吧。
Ask the homeowners to let go of the baking.
地球人研究报告。
Earthman Study Report.
趣闻。
Interesting news.
疫情期间，所有被迫关在家的人不得不面临一个重要的生存问题：吃什么。
During the epidemic, all those forced to stay at home had to face an important survival issue: what to eat.
。
.
第一梯队的方面食品在这个时候早就已经被摧枯拉朽般消耗殆尽，进阶级的“家常菜”梯队在重压下也锻炼出来了不少新战士。
By this time the first echelons of food had been consumed, and the ranks of the "home-cooked" echelons of the bourgeoisie had, under the weight of the burden, trained quite a few new soldiers.
。
.
但这还远远不够，最近一段时间，朋友圈那帮神仙们终于把魔爪伸向了“烘焙”。
But that's not enough. Recently, the party of friends and fairies has finally extended their claws to "bake."
。
.
准备工作。
Preparatory work.
2月中旬，湖南卫视主持人何炅在一档综艺节目中，演示自己如何用身边常见的东西来制作小蛋糕。
In mid-February, Hunan TV host Kyung Ho demonstrated how to make small cake with common things around him in a variety show.
一时间，何炅的小蛋糕开始被许多网友争相模仿，还登上了微博热搜。
For a time, Kyung Ho's small cake began to be many netizens competing to imitate, but also boarded Weibo hot search.
。
.
此时，过年期间的“凉皮热潮”已经退居二线，烘焙热潮的第一个冲锋号算是吹响了。
At this point, the "cool skin craze" during the New Year has retreated to the second line, the baking boom of the first sub-machine is blowing.
。
.
细想来，烘焙能在这个时候神奇的成为了厨房新宠，不是没有道理。
On second thought, baking can magically become a new favorite in the kitchen at this time, not for no reason.
。
.
这段期间想要挑战厨房的人民群众主要有两大核心需求：一是要足够消耗时间；二是要获得高于“家常菜”的烹饪品质（最好还能发朋友圈）的东西。
There are two main core needs of the people who want to challenge the kitchen during this period: one is to consume enough time; the other is to get something that is better than "home cooking" (preferably with friends).
如此，工序简单、难度不大（看起来）的烘焙就成了这个世界线收束的必经之路。
In this way, simple, easy (and seemingly) baking is the way to wrap up the world's strands.
。
.
但一切的前提，是要顺利进行烘焙过程中最关键的准备工作——打蛋——只有将分离出来的蛋清搅拌成奶油状，这样做出来的蛋糕才能更加暄软。
But the premise is that the most critical preparation for a smooth roasting process - beating eggs - is to mix the separated egg whites into butter so that the cake is more sociable.
2020年，打蛋这种机械的工作如果还要人类抽搐自己的双手来进行，就未免太不体面了。
In 2020, it would be disgraceful if the mechanical job of beating eggs were to be carried out with human hands twitching.
可是电动打蛋器对于中国厨房而言，又不普及，咋办？。
But electric beater for Chinese kitchen, and not popular, how to do?
呵呵，这点难度，在人民群众的智慧面前，无非是再一次给他们大肆发挥主观能动性的机会。
Ha ha, this difficulty, in the face of the wisdom of the masses, is nothing more than to give them the opportunity to play a large subjective initiative.
。
.
看吧，很快中国各个不知名的角落里，一个个“迷之打蛋器”如雨后春笋般腾空出世了：。
See, soon China's various unknown corners, a "bewildered egg beater" like a mushrooming out of the air:
用塑料瓶制成的打蛋器是现在网络上最常见的，也是一些美食博主推荐的常用方法。
Egg-throwers made from plastic bottles are now the most common on the Internet and recommended by some gastronomic bloggers.
不过为了提高效率，有人还想出了更硬核的手段——将电钻改造成打蛋器。
But to improve efficiency, some have come up with a harder way to turn the driller into an egg beater.
。
.
电钻这方法听上去诡异，实际效果很好，相比于其他自制打蛋器，这个办法在社交媒体上的受欢迎程度甚至仅次于塑料瓶。
The drill sounds bizarre and works well, and is even more popular on social media than other home-made beaters.
。
.
不过电钻也不是家家都有，又有人犯难了，难道没有替代品吗？哼，咱国产网友有的是办法，您瞧着：。
But electric drill is not every family, and some people are puzzled, is there no substitute? Humph, we have a home-made net friends, you see:
把电风扇拆了一样可以做打蛋器。
Remove the fan as if it were a beater.
电风扇做打蛋器的成功就像一个科学里程碑，这意味着，但凡能转的，能震动的，都有做成打蛋器的潜质。
The success of an electric fan as an egg beater is like a scientific milestone, which means that anything that can turn or vibrate has the potential to make a beater.
。
.
于是一次机械朋克向的改装风刮起来了：。
So a mechanical punk in the direction of the modification of the wind up:.
晾衣架拉二胡式打蛋器。
Pull the erhu type beater on the clothes hanger.
剃须刀，电动牙刷这些都是可以震动的物品，拆解安装一下都能做打蛋器。
Shaving razors, electric toothbrushes -- these are vibrating objects that can be used as an egg beater if dismantled and installed.
。
.
好的上面这些我还是可以理解的了，可是下面这个是什么玩意？。
All right, I can understand all this, but what's this thing down here?
四驱车打蛋器？！。
Raider Buggies?!
看见了吗，只要是能转的玩具，几乎没有一个能脱离苦海，全都拖不过要被充公拿去劳改。
See, when it comes to twirling toys, almost no one gets out of trouble, and all of them have to be confiscated and put through labor.
。
.
仔细看，这个东西其实是用来转陀螺的↓。
Look carefully, this thing is actually used to turn the top.
太惨烈了，他们还都是孩子（们玩的玩具）啊。
It's terrible. They're all kids.
。
.
尽管不排除其中有人只是借机作秀，但网友这解决问题的阵势，如果继续发展下去，后果恐不堪设想：。
Although does not rule out that some of them just take the opportunity to show off, but the netizens this solution situation, if continues to develop, the consequences may be unthinkable:
想象一下吧，当老外走在大街上，看见中国老百姓从手上掏出这个玩意，会有什么感叹——。
Imagine, when foreigners walk in the street, see the Chinese people out of the hands of this gadget, will have a sigh -.
实操。
Fuck it.
准备工作解决后，一切准备就绪，下面就要拿出真本事了。
After the preparations are made, everything is ready, and the next step is to show your ability.
。
.
那么，烹饪神仙们有本事吗？。
So, do the cooking fairies have the ability?
可太有了↓。
How much I have.
1，美妙的一刻开始了：。
1. The moment of beauty begins.
“安倍怕了，奥巴马惊了，特朗普急了。
"Abe is afraid, Obama is startled, and Trump is impatient.
”。
"
惊悚惊悚在，老外永远想不到，一个普普通通的厨用电器，在经过中国老百姓的改装后，可以发挥出多么大的杀伤力。
Thriller thriller, foreigners can never think of, a common kitchen appliances, after the transformation of the Chinese people, can play how much lethal.
。
.
能把电饭煲改装成迫击炮的匠人。
A craftsman who can convert rice cookers into mortars.
他们同样想不到的是，一个仅靠“烘焙”制成的食物，能够在形态上存在着多么丰富的可能性。
They also wondered how much more morphological possibilities there were for a single "roasted" food.
。
.
中国的厨房中，似乎蕴藏着比精密化学实验室的更多更刁钻的催化物质。
China's kitchens seem to contain more tricky catalytic substances than sophisticated chemical laboratories.
。
.
同样的设备，不同的结果，这就是腰间盘突出的“烘焙匠人”们能探索到的碳水化合物状态的极限：。
The same device, with different results, is the limit of carbohydrate status that the lumbar disc protruding from the baker can explore:
看上去很难拔下来。
It looks hard to unplug.
做成功的蛋糕都没这块圆吧。
You can't make a successful cake without it.
那么，除了在物理形态上做文章，“烘焙匠人”在烘焙产品的视觉感官上有没有建树呢？。
So, apart from writing about the physical form, does the baker make a difference in the visual sense of the baked product?
你好，有的。
Hello, yes.
。
.
比如下面这个。
Like this one below.
就算是块电饭煲蛋糕，它也能做出让人不适的形状。
Even an electric rice cooker can make an uncomfortable shape.
。
.
本身形状没有问题的，也要努力朝着奇怪的方向发展。
If you have no problem with your shape, try to move in a strange direction.
。
.
一位网友用一句话总结了自己做面点的经历，收获了上千个赞：。
A netizen summed up his experience of making noodle with one sentence and gained thousands of praise:
与此同时，“烘焙”产物的近亲们日子也不算好过。
Meanwhile, close relatives of "baked" products are not doing well either.
惨烈状况几乎不能用成句的语言描述，只能汇聚成一个个代表性的名词：。
Tragedy conditions can hardly be described in terms of sentences, only to converge into a representative noun:.
“地狱包子”。
"Hell's bastard."
。
.
这才是反派面食该有的样子。
That's what a pasta dish looks like.
“涅槃面包”。
"Nirvana Bread."
。
.
“实在编不出来词的油条”。
It's hard to make up a stick of words.
。
.
我仿佛能看到烹饪圈“面点黑暗帝国”的迷雾正从空中浩荡袭来。
It seemed to me that the "dark empire of noodle" of cookery circles was coming through the air.
。
.
因为时间充足，广大网友对面食的研究似乎没有浅尝辄止的迹象。
Because the time is sufficient, the vast majority of netizens to pasta research seems to have no signs of shallow stop.
根据官方报道，疫情期间面粉销量上涨9倍，有媒体甚至打出了“面粉销量堪比口罩”的标题。
According to official reports, flour sales increased tenfold during the epidemic, with some outlets even carrying the headline "Flour sells like a mask."
。
.
如今凉皮蛋糕的热度不减当时，油条刚刚“上位”成功，台下还有双皮奶、珍珠奶茶、舒芙蕾等等“选手”蓄势待发。
Now the heat of the cold skin cake did not reduce the time, just "upper" success, there are double skin milk, pearl milk tea, Shuvlei and other "players" ready to go.
看起来国人对于食物的热情，伴随着疫情的发展，一时半会看来还难以散去。
It seems that people's enthusiasm for food, along with the spread of the epidemic, will not seem to dissipate for a while.
。
.
或许等疫情结束，人人都变身“大厨”，餐厅也无需担忧，厨子们也不用焦虑，忙碌的工作肯定会让大家重新聚集在原来的地方，一切依然会回到原来的轨迹上。
Perhaps by the time the epidemic is over, everyone will be a chef, restaurants won't have to worry, and cooks won't have to worry. Busy jobs will surely get people back where they are and everything will be back on track.
。
.
只是，这一切都要寄希望于，自家厨房能够撑到那一天的到来。
All this, however, is in the hope that our kitchen will hold out until that day.
。
.
